Russian Movers: Aeroflot, Evraz Group, Rusal Shares Are Active

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-03-31T16:16:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/russian-movers-aeroflot-evraz-group-rusal-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.1
percent to 1,813.59 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index gained for a second day, adding 0.4
percent, to 2,044.20.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Aeroflot (AFLT RX),  Russia ’s biggest airline, climbed
the most in two weeks, adding 1.8 percent to 73.4 rubles. The
company said yesterday it may post a profit of 10.5 billion
rubles ($369 million) for 2010.  Evraz Group SA (EVR)  , Russia’s second-biggest
steelmaker, partly owned by  Roman Abramovich , advanced 1 percent
to $39.70 in London trading, headed for its highest close since
Feb 8. The company reported net income was $548 million last
year versus a loss of $295 million in 2009. That’s double the
$272 million average estimate of 16 analysts in a Bloomberg
survey.  United Co. Rusal (RUALR RX), the world’s largest aluminum
maker, surged to its highest in four weeks, gaining 3.9 percent
to 486.52 rubles after tripling profit and beating estimates.
Net income was $2.87 billion, or 19 cents a share, from $821
million, or 6 cents, a year earlier. The median estimate of 13
analysts compiled by Bloomberg was for profit of $2.02 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
